columns.name: name
columns.description: The name of the Web ACL. You cannot change the name of a Web ACL after you create it.

columns.name: arn
columns.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the entity.

columns.name: web_acl_id
columns.description: The unique identifier for the Web ACL.

columns.name: default_action
columns.description: The action to perform if none of the Rules contained in the WebACL match.

columns.name: metric_name
columns.description: A friendly name or description for the metrics for this WebACL.

columns.name: logging_configuration
columns.description: The logging configuration for the web ACL.

columns.name: resources
columns.description: An array of ARNs (Amazon Resource Names) of the resources associated with the web ACL.

columns.name: rules
columns.description: The Rule statements used to identify the web requests that you want to allow, block, or count.

columns.name: tags_src
columns.description: A list of tags associated with the resource.
